## Architecture Summary

### Data Flow
Google Sheets (tabs = customer groups)
  → each tab: B2=groupName, C3+=dates, F3+=totalSpent, G3+=remaining, H3+=accountIDs
  → H row (today's row): per-account spent values (H[rowIndex], I[rowIndex], ...)
  → Electron reads → classifies → sets FB spend_cap via Marketing API

### Key Files
- `electron/services/googleSheetsService.ts`  — sheet reads + callWithRetry
- `electron/services/facebookService.ts`       — setSpendingLimit / clearSpendingLimit
- `electron/services/configService.ts`         — config persistence (userData/config.json)
- `electron/services/schedulerService.ts`      — interval-based scheduler (N hours)
- `electron/services/updaterService.ts`        — electron-updater GitHub releases
- `electron/services/limitCacheService.ts`     — exists, NOT used by main loop
- `electron/ipcHandlers.ts`                    — executeForGroups + all IPC handlers
- `electron/preload.ts`                        — renderer bridge
- `src/types/index.ts`                         — shared types
- `src/components/SettingsPanel.tsx`           — config UI
- `src/components/SchedulePanel.tsx`           — schedule status UI
- `src/components/UpdateBadge.tsx`             — auto-update badge
- `src/hooks/useUpdater.ts`                    — update state hook
- `src/pages/Index.tsx`                        — main page
- `scripts/build-electron.mjs`                 — esbuild CJS bundler

