## AppConfiguration (src/types/index.ts)

```typescript
{
  googleSheetId: string
  serviceAccountPath: string
  facebookApiToken: string
  excludedTabs: string                  // comma-sep system tabs to skip
  scheduleEnabled: boolean
  scheduleIntervalHours: number         // default 2
  scheduleIncludedGroups: string[]      // INCLUSION list — empty = all skipped
  maxBuffer: number                     // default 100 — cap per account ($)
  autoRevokeInactive: boolean           // default true
}
```

### Default excluded system tabs (excludedTabs field):
`Configuration, RAW Data Aggregated, Dashboard Summary, Dashboard Summary (VNĐ),
Ads Rules Status, Update Money, Update Money 1, CustomMessage, Bảng Tổng Hợp, USD mẫu`

================================================================================
## Classification Algorithm (executeForGroups in ipcHandlers.ts)

```
For each tab in scheduleIncludedGroups:
  - Wait 1200ms (throttle: ~50 reads/min, quota=60/min)
  - parseTab() → GroupData { accountIds, remaining, spent, accountSpentMap }

  getSpent(id) = accountSpentMap[id] ?? groupSpent ?? 0

  activeAccounts  = filter(id => getSpent(id) > 0.01)
  inactiveAccounts = filter(id => getSpent(id) <= 0.01)

  CASE A (all $0, start of day):
    fundedAccounts = ALL accounts
    limit = min(maxBuffer, remaining / N)  — equal split

  CASE B (≥1 account has Spent > 0):
    fundedAccounts = activeAccounts
    revokedAccounts = inactiveAccounts
    totalActiveSpent = sum(getSpent for active)
    limit[id] = min(maxBuffer, accountSpent[id] / totalActiveSpent × remaining)  — proportional

  Step 2: setSpendingLimit(id, limit)  for all funded
  Step 3: clearSpendingLimit(id)       for inactive (if autoRevokeInactive=true)
```

### FB API calls:
- Set limit:   `POST /v24.0/act_{ID}?spend_cap={float}&access_token={token}`
- Delete limit: `POST /v24.0/act_{ID}?spend_cap_action=delete&access_token={token}`

================================================================================
## Google Sheets Quota Management

### callWithRetry (googleSheetsService.ts)
- Catches: HTTP 429, "Quota exceeded", "RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED"
- Backoff: 2s → 4s → 8s (3 retries)

### executeForGroups loop
- 1200ms delay per tab → ~50 reads/min

### sheets:fetch (Refresh button)
- `Promise.allSettled` — fires all concurrently (for speed, UI-only use)
- callWithRetry handles any occasional 429

================================================================================
## Completed Changes This Session (2026-04-05 → 2026-04-07)

### 1. clearSpendingLimit — correct FB API param
- Was: `spend_cap=0` (removes cap → unlimited)
- Fixed: `spend_cap_action=delete`
- curl: `POST https://graph.facebook.com/v24.0/act_xxx?access_token=TOKEN&spend_cap_action=delete`

### 2. Schedule: Excluded → Included groups
- `scheduleExcludedGroups` renamed to `scheduleIncludedGroups` everywhere
- Default `[]` = all groups skipped (opt-in model)
- UI: "Groups Included in Schedule" with green badges; "None selected (all skipped)"
- ipcHandlers: `allTabs.filter(t => included.includes(t))`

### 3. Per-account spent classification
- googleSheetsService: range changed `H3:ZZ3` → `H3:ZZ300` to read full block
- Row 0 = account IDs; row[rowIndex] = per-account spent for today
- GroupData: added `accountSpentMap?: Record<string, number>`
- Classification now per-account (not tab-level aggregate)

### 4. Proportional limit allocation (Case B)
- Was: flat `remaining / N_active` cap for all active
- Now: `min(maxBuffer, accountSpent[id] / totalActiveSpent × remaining)` per account
- Case A unchanged: equal split (no ratio data yet)

### 5. Google Sheets quota fixes
- googleSheetsService: `callWithRetry` with exponential backoff
- executeForGroups: 1200ms inter-tab delay
- sheets:fetch: reverted to `Promise.allSettled` (fast, for UI only)

